---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Asko Dishwasher Repair | Southern California | Swedish Luxury XXL";
const description = "Asko dishwasher repair across SoCal, Swedish heritage, Hisense-owned via Gorenje, XXL Hidden Display, Turbo Combi Drying. Same-day diagnostic.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/asko-dishwasher-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Asko still Swedish? I thought they were bought by a Chinese company.",
    a: "Asko's identity is Swedish-heritage design, but the manufacturing and ownership structure has evolved. Asko was founded in Sweden in 1950 (Jung, Sweden, the brand name is an acronym of the founder's wife Anna-Stina Karlsson's initials + the Swedish word for laundry). Slovenian Gorenje Group acquired Asko in July 2010 and transferred production of all Asko appliances from Sweden to Slovenia in 2013. Chinese company Hisense then acquired a 95% majority stake in Gorenje Group in June 2018. So current Asko dishwashers are: Swedish-designed and engineered (the Asko design studio and engineering identity remain Scandinavian), Slovenian-manufactured (production in Velenje, Slovenia), and owned through Gorenje by Hisense. Service-chain implication for LA: Asko parts route through Gorenje's US distribution (operated under Hisense Americas since 2018) rather than direct Swedish-sourced channels, meaningful for parts lead time on specialty items (5-10 day typical)."
  },
  {
    q: "Asko is positioned as luxury, is that really justified compared to Miele or Bosch 800 Series?",
    a: "Asko's luxury positioning is anchored on specific feature choices that differentiate it from the German-engineering luxury tier (Miele + Bosch 800 Series), and our honest field read is that it's justified in specific use cases, not universally. Asko's signature features: (1) XXL-capacity interior, genuinely larger usable space than standard 24\" dishwashers, with Flexi Racks three-level or four-level loading systems; fits fine-dining cookware, large serving platters, half-hotel pans; (2) Turbo Combi Drying with fan-assisted evacuation + auto door opening, drier final-stage performance than standard condensation drying; (3) Scandinavian design aesthetic, stainless-steel construction throughout, fully-integrated panel-ready options. Pricing runs $1,500-$3,000+, overlapping the mid-to-upper Bosch 800 Series range and the lower-to-mid Miele tier. For Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Hollywood Hills fine-dining residential kitchens where XXL capacity actually matters, Asko earns its position. For general mid-premium use, Miele and Bosch 800 Series offer comparable service life at similar price points with stronger US parts networks."
  },
  {
    q: "What Asko dishwasher models are most common in LA?",
    a: "By volume, Asko's 50-Series and 60+Series fully-integrated XXL dishwashers dominate our LA Asko service. 50-Series is the mainstream premium tier, three-level Flexi Racks, 40 dB noise, Turbo Combi Drying, Status Light door-projection, connectivity. 60+Series is the step-up, four-level Flexi Racks, 39 dB noise, Auto Dose detergent dispensing, push-to-open door, enhanced connectivity. Both tiers are panel-ready as the core configuration (stainless-front variants exist but design-forward LA kitchens typically spec panel-ready). DFI565 and DFI786 model families are common call-outs. Pro Handle trim on stainless-front units (DBI family) shows up in mid-premium kitchen refreshes. XXL capacity + Turbo Combi Drying is the feature combination our techs see on the majority of calls, that's the Asko value proposition for LA households that spec Asko."
  },
  {
    q: "Asko vs Miele, two Scandinavian-European luxury dishwashers. What's the real difference?",
    a: "Two luxury tier dishwashers with different parent structures and service realities. <b>Miele</b>, German family-owned (Gütersloh, since 1899), reference-luxury positioning, German-engineering platform, 20-year design life, US parts network through Miele USA (Princeton NJ). Service premium but parts reliably sourced. See <a href='/brands/miele-dishwasher-repair/'>Miele dishwasher repair</a>. <b>Asko</b>, Swedish heritage + Slovenian manufacturing + Hisense ownership (via Gorenje 2018), tested for 20 years of use per Asko specification, Scandinavian-design platform, US parts via Gorenje Americas distribution. XXL-capacity advantage on higher-trim models. Pricing overlaps the Miele tier but trends slightly lower at comparable feature levels. For LA service: Miele's parts network is deeper and faster; Asko's parts network is adequate for common items, 5-10 day typical for specialty parts. Service-life expectations comparable on both. The choice often comes down to: Miele for reference-luxury recognition + maximum parts-network depth; Asko for XXL capacity + Scandinavian design + slight price relief."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Asko won't start and the Status Light is showing an error code, where do we start?",
    a: "Asko's Status Light door-projection system doubles as a diagnostic indicator when a fault is present. Our diagnostic approach: (1) verify the fault code via the Asko code reference for your specific series (50-Series vs 60+Series error codes differ); common codes F1 / F2 / F3 / F4 map to water-fill, drain, heating, and control-board faults respectively; (2) check water supply, dishwasher won't start fill cycle if supply is blocked or the water-inlet valve has failed; valve swap $240–$380; (3) check door interlock, compressed or misaligned door triggers start-lockout; adjustment $120–$180 or latch + interlock service $220–$360; (4) control-board fault if (1)-(3) are clean, Asko control boards have their own platform (not BSH or Whirlpool chassis), specialty parts 7-14 day typical lead; swap $440–$680 depending on generation; (5) main interface panel (higher-trim Status Light controller) failures separate from core control board; panel $360–$540. Our techs carry Asko-specific diagnostic tools in dispatch, the platform requires brand-specific knowledge that doesn't transfer from Bosch or Samsung dishwasher service."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Asko dishwasher repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Asko bands: drain filter clean (often free at diagnostic) $89 if no other work; drain pump replacement $220–$360 (Asko pump design slightly different from common US-platform pumps); water-inlet valve $240–$380; door latch + interlock $220–$360; door gasket (panel-ready vs stainless-front profiles differ) $280–$460; heating element $280–$440; Turbo Combi Drying fan motor $320–$480 (feature-specific to higher-trim Asko); spray arm replacement $180–$300; Flexi Racks rail + roller service $160–$280 (rack hardware wear at 6-8 years on daily-use households); circulation pump $440–$620; main control board $440–$680; Status Light / interface panel $360–$540; compressor-to-inverter (heat-pump drying higher trim) $480–$720. Asko parts sourcing through Gorenje Americas channel runs 5-10 days typical on common service items, 7-14 days on Asko-specific specialty parts. First-visit repair rate is strong on drain + door + spray-arm service (we carry Asko-compatible parts in dispatch); control-board and specialty parts are second-visit completion after parts arrive."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Asko Dishwasher Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Asko Dishwasher Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Asko dishwasher repair across Los Angeles, Swedish heritage + Slovenian manufacturing + Hisense-owned via Gorenje. 50-Series and 60+Series XXL fully-integrated panel-ready, Turbo Combi Drying, Flexi Racks, Status Light. Fine-dining residential kitchen service focus across Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Hollywood Hills. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Asko", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/asko/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Asko Dishwasher Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Asko XXL dishwasher service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Asko › Dishwasher Repair</div>
          <h1>Asko Dishwasher Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Asko is the Swedish-heritage luxury dishwasher specialist. Founded in 1950 in Jung, Sweden;
            acquired by Slovenian Gorenje Group in 2010; Gorenje itself acquired by Chinese Hisense in
            2018 (Hisense now holds 95% of Gorenje). Asko production transferred from Sweden to
            Slovenia in 2013, so current Asko dishwashers are Swedish-designed / Slovenian-manufactured /
            Hisense-owned-via-Gorenje. For LA, Asko's XXL-capacity Flexi Racks, Turbo Combi Drying, and
            Scandinavian design aesthetic find their natural home in fine-dining residential kitchens ,
            Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Hollywood Hills, Brentwood, Manhattan Beach,
            Malibu, where the cookware size justifies oversized capacity and the design aesthetic
            matches. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Swedish heritage since 1950</b>, Slovenian-made since 2013, Hisense-owned via Gorenje since 2018</li>
            <li><b>XXL capacity + Turbo Combi Drying</b>, signature feature combination for fine-dining kitchens</li>
            <li><b>50-Series + 60+Series specialists</b>, fully-integrated panel-ready service</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Asko in LA, Swedish-heritage luxury for fine-dining kitchens</h2>
      <p>
        Asko's LA installed base concentrates in fine-dining residential kitchens, households where
        the cookware is genuinely large (serving platters, sheet pans, whole roasting pans, fine-china
        sets) and the kitchen design spec calls for panel-ready fully-integrated appliances that
        disappear into the cabinetry. That's the Beverly Hills / Bel Air / Pacific Palisades / Hollywood
        Hills / Brentwood market where kitchen budgets support $2,000-$3,000+ dishwashers and the XXL
        capacity justifies the spend. Secondary volume: Manhattan Beach and Malibu coastal luxury,
        Calabasas and Hidden Hills Valley luxury, Newport Beach and Laguna Beach Orange County luxury.
        Our techs see Asko primarily in kitchens where Miele was also considered and Asko won on
        capacity or design preference.
      </p>
      <p>
        The corporate structure matters for parts + service. Asko parts route through Gorenje Americas
        distribution (operated under Hisense Americas since 2018). That channel is adequate for common
        service items (drain pumps, spray arms, gaskets, heating elements, 5-10 day typical lead) and
        supports specialty items (control boards, Turbo Combi Drying fan modules, Status Light
        interfaces, 7-14 day typical lead). Asko platforms don't share chassis with Bosch (BSH) or
        Whirlpool-family dishwashers, the service approach, diagnostic tooling, and parts inventory
        are brand-specific. Our dispatch carries Asko-compatible common parts; specialty parts are
        second-visit completion after parts arrive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Asko dishwasher failures our techs see most often</h2>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door latch + interlock service on 5-7 year units</h3>
        <p>
          Asko's door interlock system, which prevents start while the door is open and detects door
          position for cycle-progress, occasionally fails mechanically or drifts out of calibration.
          Swap + adjustment $220–$360. Common 5-7 year service item on daily-use luxury-kitchen installs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Drain pump + filter service</h3>
        <p>
          LA hard water + fine-china food debris produce drain-filter buildup and occasional drain-pump
          impeller wear. Filter clean often free at diagnostic; pump swap $220–$360 when mechanical
          fault confirmed (Asko pump design slightly different from common US platforms).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Turbo Combi Drying fan + auto-door-opening service</h3>
        <p>
          Asko's Turbo Combi Drying uses fan-assisted moisture evacuation plus automatic door opening
          at cycle end. Fan motor failures present as dishes coming out damp even with correct detergent
          and rinse aid use. Fan motor swap $320–$480. Auto-door-opening actuator service separate
          $240–$380 when door doesn't pop at cycle end.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Flexi Racks rail + roller wear at 6-8 years</h3>
        <p>
          Asko's Flexi Racks three-level (50-Series) or four-level (60+Series) adjustable rack system
          relies on smooth-rolling rail + roller hardware. Wear at 6-8 years on daily-use households
          produces sticky rack movement. Service $160–$280 for rail + roller replacement and
          alignment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Control board + Status Light interface (specialty parts)</h3>
        <p>
          Main control board faults rare but specialty when they occur, Asko platform doesn't share
          with Whirlpool or BSH. Board swap $440–$680, 7-14 day part lead time typical. Status Light
          door-projection interface panel separate from core control board; swap $360–$540 when the
          Status Light system fails independently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Heating element + heat-pump drying service (higher trim)</h3>
        <p>
          Standard heating element swap $280–$440 on resistance-heat models. Higher-trim Asko with
          heat-pump drying system requires compressor-to-inverter service at $480–$720 when the drying
          system fails (distinct from the heating element serving the wash cycle).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Asko dishwasher product lines we service</h2>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>50-Series fully-integrated XXL</h3>
          <p>Asko's mainstream premium tier. Three-level Flexi Racks, 40 dB noise, Turbo Combi Drying,
          Status Light door projection, connectivity. Panel-ready as core configuration. DFI565 model
          family common call-outs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>60+Series fully-integrated XXL</h3>
          <p>Step-up premium tier. Four-level Flexi Racks, 39 dB noise, Auto Dose detergent
          dispensing, push-to-open door, enhanced connectivity. Panel-ready. DFI786 model family.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Pro Handle stainless-front (DBI family)</h3>
          <p>Stainless-front variants with Pro Handle trim for kitchens that spec exposed dishwasher
          aesthetic rather than panel-ready. Mid-premium kitchen refreshes common application.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Flexi Racks adjustable loading</h3>
          <p>Asko's signature rack system, three-level on 50-Series, four-level on 60+Series. Designed
          for XXL capacity with fine-dining cookware accommodation. Rack hardware service at 6-8 years.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Turbo Combi Drying system</h3>
          <p>Fan-assisted moisture evacuation + auto door opening at cycle end. Asko-signature feature
          that differentiates dry-performance from standard condensation drying. Specialty service for
          fan motor + auto-door actuator.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Status Light + connectivity</h3>
          <p>Door-projection indicator + app connectivity on higher-trim Asko. Specialty service path
          for Status Light interface separate from core control board.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Asko vs Miele vs Bosch 800 Series, the premium dishwasher comparison</h2>
      <p>
        Three platforms dominate premium US dishwasher installs. Each has distinct parent structure,
        service implications, and feature priorities.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Miele</b>, German family-owned (Gütersloh since 1899), reference-luxury positioning,
        deepest US parts network, 20-year design life. Highest service-network depth. See
        <a href="/brands/miele-dishwasher-repair/">Miele dishwasher repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Bosch 800 Series</b>, BSH Home Appliances (Bosch Siemens Hausgeräte), German-engineered,
        Third Rack + CrystalDry + AutoAir service features, US parts through BSH broad dealer network.
        See <a href="/brands/bosch-dishwasher-repair/">Bosch dishwasher repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Asko (this page)</b>, Swedish heritage + Slovenian manufacturing + Hisense-owned-via-
        Gorenje, XXL capacity + Turbo Combi Drying feature emphasis, fine-dining kitchen focus.
      </p>
      <p>
        Choice drivers: Miele for reference-luxury recognition + deepest parts network; Bosch 800
        Series for German-engineering mid-premium + broadest US dealer support; Asko for XXL
        capacity + Scandinavian design + price relief vs. Miele at comparable features. All three
        serviced by our team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Asko dishwasher repair typically costs</h2>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drain filter clean</td><td>$89</td><td>Often free at diagnostic when no other work</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drain pump replacement</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>Asko-platform specific</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water-inlet valve</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Fill-cycle fault</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door latch + interlock</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>5-7 year service item</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (panel-ready / stainless profiles)</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>Profile-specific sourcing</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Heating element</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Resistance-heat models</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Turbo Combi Drying fan motor</td><td>$320 – $480</td><td>Higher-trim signature</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Auto-door-opening actuator</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Cycle-end door pop</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Spray arm replacement</td><td>$180 – $300</td><td>Upper or lower</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Flexi Racks rail + roller</td><td>$160 – $280</td><td>6-8 year wear pattern</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Circulation pump</td><td>$440 – $620</td><td>8-plus-year service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$440 – $680</td><td>7-14 day part lead typical</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Status Light / interface panel</td><td>$360 – $540</td><td>Specialty higher-trim</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Heat-pump drying service</td><td>$480 – $720</td><td>Higher-trim feature</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader reference: <a href="/price-list/dishwasher-repair-cost/">dishwasher repair cost
        guide</a>. Related pages: <a href="/brands/miele-dishwasher-repair/">Miele dishwasher repair
        (luxury alternative)</a>, <a href="/brands/bosch-dishwasher-repair/">Bosch dishwasher repair
        (800 Series)</a>, <a href="/brands/beko-dishwasher-repair/">Beko dishwasher repair
        (Arçelik family)</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Service areas, where our Asko calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>Westside fine-dining kitchens (Asko heartland)</h4>
          <p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · Brentwood · Pacific Palisades · <a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a></p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Hollywood Hills + canyon luxury</h4>
          <p>Hollywood Hills · Laurel Canyon · Outpost Estates · Nichols Canyon · Mount Olympus</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Coastal luxury</h4>
          <p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes Estates · Rolling Hills</p>
